## 4. Posing standards → measurable parameters (from web research)

### Open / Classic mandatories

**Front Double Biceps** — orientation: front.
- Elbows slightly **above** shoulder line → elbow_y above shoulder_y.
- Forearms **perpendicular to ground** → elbow→wrist segment ≈ vertical.
- Fists near shoulders → elbow flexion acute (~30–60°).
- Stance ~shoulder-width, knees pushed out → ankle-sep ratio + knee-out ratio.
- Symmetry: L/R elbow height, L/R elbow angle, L/R forearm angle, shoulder line level.

**Front Lat Spread** — orientation: front.
- Arms extended to sides, **parallel to ground** → upper-arm ≈ horizontal, elbows ≈ shoulder height.
- Elbows near-straight → elbow flexion ~150–180°.
- Symmetry: L/R upper-arm angle, elbow height.

**Side Chest** — orientation: side (reduced confidence; skip symmetry).
- Front leg bent, **front heel raised**, back leg straight → front knee flexion + ankle-height delta.
- Torso rotated to profile → orientation check confirms side.

**Side Triceps** — orientation: side.
- Front upper arm against side, back arm reaches small of back → wrist-near-hip (back arm).
- Front leg flexed, heel lifted, back leg straight → front knee flexion + heel raise.

**Rear Double Biceps** — orientation: rear.
- Same arm geometry as front double biceps, from behind.
- One leg back with **heel raised** (rear calf) → ankle-height delta, knee flexion of back leg.
- Symmetry valid (rear is a frontal-style view of the back).

**Rear Lat Spread** — orientation: rear.
- Elbows flared forward, hands at lower lats / waist → wrist-near-hip, elbow-out.
- Stance width; symmetry of elbow position.

**Abdominal & Thigh** — orientation: front.
- Common variant: **both hands behind head** (wrist-near-ear small), elbows flared.
- One thigh extended forward → one knee straighter / one ankle forward.

**Most Muscular (crab)** — orientation: front.
- Hands clasped at center front → fists-together (L/R wrist distance small, near mid-torso).
- Shoulders hunched/forward → shoulder elevation.

### Men's Physique quarter turns (board-shorts divisions)

- **Front:** feet parallel, symmetry display. **One hand on hip** on side & rear turns (the rule that distinguishes physique from bodybuilding) → wrist-near-hip on the appropriate side.
- **Quarter turns:** orientation classifier verifies the user actually reaches front → right-side → rear → left-side, fluidly.
- **Side:** hips face side, head toward judges → orientation=side + head-yaw toward camera.
- **Rear:** lats spread for V-taper → elbow-out + shoulder-to-hip width ratio.

Women's divisions (Bikini, Wellness, Figure, Women's Physique) reuse the **quarter-turn
framework**; division-specific templates added in P17 as content.

